President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in Puerto Rico due to severe storms, flooding, and landslides that occurred from February 4 to February 6, 2022. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. The municipalities of Cata√±o, Dorado, Toa Baja, Vega Alta, and Vega Baja will receive federal funding, including grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other assistance programs for individuals and business owners. Hazard mitigation measures for the entire commonwealth will also receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis. Deanne Criswell, Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), has appointed Robert Little III as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing in other areas, and additional assistance may be designated once the assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance starting tomorrow through the Disaster Assistance website or by calling the provided toll-free numbers. The FEMA News Desk can be contacted for further information.